title: No Knead Soft Dinner Rolls | Very Fast Bread Dough
description:
Soft No Knead Dinner Rolls | Very Fast Bread Dough
These Soft No Knead Dinner Rolls are so easy to make and so delicious! All you need is one spoon and few ingredients!
Please find below the Soft No Knead Dinner Rolls recipe and if you want to see more don't forget to subscribe!

Ingredients:
• 600 g all-purpose flour
• 280 ml Warm Milk
• 7g dry yeast
• 2 tablespoons Sugar
• 2 Eggs
• 100g Soften Butter
• 1 teaspoon Salt


Step 1: 
In a medium bowl add the warm milk, the dry yeast, the sugar and stir until well-combined.

Step 2: 
Add the beaten yolks, the soften butter, the salt and gradually the flour. Stir until the dough is formed.

Step 3: 
Transfer the dough on a bowl greased with butter. Cover with plastic foil and let it rest in a warm place for 2 hours until double sized.

Step 4:
Sprinkle flour on the working surface, place the dough and cut into 8 pieces. Form into rolls and place on a greased tray. Cover with plastic foil and let it rise for another 40 minutes at room temperature. 

Step 5:
Grease the rolls with a mixture of a beaten yolk and 1 tbsp of milk. 

Step 6:
Preheat the oven to 190°C and bake for 20 minutes.

Enjoy!
